ist. In North America, this surname has also absorbed various cognates from other languages, e.g. German   Steffen  , German and Polish   Stefan  , Slovenian and Slovak <b>Štefan</b>, Hungarian <b>István</b> (see   Istvan  ), and also their patronymics and other derivatives (see   Stevens  )."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Henry Stevens was born in 1510, in Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Elizabeth Andrews. He died on 22 October 1587, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1510–22 October 1587":"1510–22. oktoober 1587","1510–1587":"1510–1587","1531–1643":"1531–1643","1643":"1643","1510":"1510","1587":"1587","1531":"1531","22 October 1587":"22. oktoober 1587","5 Aug 1587":"5. august 1587","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Exeter, Devon, England":"Exeter, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1510–22 October 1587":"1510–22. lokakuuta 1587","1510–1587":"1510–1587","1531–1643":"1531–1643","1643":"1643","1510":"1510","1587":"1587","1531":"1531","22 October 1587":"22. lokakuuta 1587","5 Aug 1587":"5. elokuuta 1587","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Exeter, Devon, England":"Exeter, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1510–22 October 1587":"1510–22 octobre 1587","1510–1587":"1510–1587","1531–1643":"1531–1643","1643":"1643",